summary: Executive profile: forward-thinking senior leader with expertise in marketing, partner acquisition, contract negotiation, communications, project management, collaboration and consensus building; MBA holder with extensive experience in discounts programs, partner marketing and strategic growth.

experience.title: DIRECTOR
experience.description: Lead discounts initiatives involving technology, branding, marketing, strategy development and evaluation of new member benefit programs; collaborate with clubs on partner marketing, branding, technology efforts, contract negotiations and partner acquisition; lead multiple club work teams; develop topics for the Discounts Sub-Committee; oversee vendor evaluation for the discounts technology solution; oversee multi-channel marketing materials; provide analytics and insights on partner performance; lead sales acquisition adding brands to Show Your Card & Save program; negotiate partner contracts and launch programs.

experience.title: INTERNET DEVELOPMENT PROJECT MANAGER
experience.description: Managed Internet project and AAA.com functionality for online travel bookings; supervised team of four developers and designers; delivered enhanced national web site on time; conducted focus groups; oversaw RFP for ISP; evaluated internet costs; collaborated to deploy Internet as a service delivery channel.

experience.title: ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING MANAGER
experience.description: Managed AOL/AAA.com projects; accelerated creative and technical development; built relationships with Internet Development Committee; managed TourBook, zip code, AAA offices and dues; created content and promotional programs; initiated online contests; developed secure web site for credit card transactions and online membership applications.

experience.title: MARKETING / PRODUCT DEVELOPMENT MANAGER
experience.description: Performed marketing and project management within Publishing; conducted financial/market feasibility for opportunities including electronic travel kiosk and multimedia venture; became Marketing Manager in 1993; developed club travel store program and direct-to-member publications sales tests; managed sponsorships and product development.

experience.title: VICE PRESIDENT BRANCH ADMINISTRATOR
experience.description: Managed operations for seven branches with 45 employees and $184 million in deposits; implemented plan to maintain customer base during government intervention.

experience.title: VICEPRESIDENT
experience.description: Directed statewide marketing for 36-branch institution; previously led marketing for Daytona region; managed $750,000 marketing budget; developed and executed marketing plans; led multimedia campaigns including a deposit-boosting campaign; launched business development program generating $14 million in sales; established outbound telemarketing department generating $2 million deposits in first months.

experience.title: BUSINESS DEVELOPMENT REPRESENTATIVE
experience.description: Created Newcomer Program to attract business; managed sales efforts generating $20 million in deposits in first five years; promoted to Vice President, Regional Marketing Manager in 1993.

experience.title: NEWSPAPER REPORTER
experience.description: Covered city government, general news and feature stories; promoted to business writer and reported on financial topics while studying for MBA.

education.degree: Bachelor of Science Degree: Journalism and Business
